<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="180" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[831,1437,1892,2077]" lastBlockId="8.[151,756,257,442]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="180" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,945,1892,1916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">Remarks:</emphasis>
This genus comprises less species in North America that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lobl &amp; Stephan" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[979,1081,1927,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1081,1927,1949]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">Baeocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the opposite is in the Old World. To date, 23 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1181,1311,1959,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1311,1959,1981]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">Scaphisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reported from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1081,1989,2013]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Newton A. F. &amp; Thayer M. K. &amp; Ashe J. S. &amp; Chandler D. S." box="[1095,1316,1989,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" pagination="272 - 418" refId="ref10261" refString="Newton A. F., Thayer M. K., Ashe J. S., Chandler D. S. 2001. 22. Superfamily Staphylinoidea Latreille, 1802 Staphyliniformia Lameere, 1900; Brachelytra auctorum. 22. Staphylinidae Latreille, 1802 (pp. 272 - 418). In: Arnett R. H., Thomas M. C. (eds). American beetles. Volume 1. Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga, Polyphaga: Staphyliniformia. CRC Press; Boca Raton, London, New York, Washington, D. C., XV + 443 pp." type="book chapter" year="2001">
Newton 
<emphasis box="[1190,1251,1991,2013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">et al.,</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
), including 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lobl, 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Lobl" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[831,1155,2021,2045]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanum">
<emphasis box="[831,999,2023,2045]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">S. americanum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[1020,1147,2021,2045]" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" pagination="385 - 391" refId="ref10008" refString="Lobl I. 1987. Contribution to the knowledge of the genus Caryoscapha Ganglbauer (Coleoptera: Scaphidiidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin 41: 385 - 391." type="journal article" year="1987">Löbl, 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
originally placed in the subsequently synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[1138,1281,2055,2077]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Caryoscapha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1281,2055,2077]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="178">Caryoscapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Leschen R. A. B. &amp; Lobl I." lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="180" pageId="6" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref9900" refString="Leschen R. A. B., Lobl I. 2005. Phylogeny and classification of Scaphisomatini Staphylinidae: Scaphidiinae with notes on mycophagy, termitophily, and functional morphology. Coleopterists Society Monographs 3: 1 - 63." type="journal article" year="2005">Leschen &amp; Löbl, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The following four species have been listed from 
<collectingRegion box="[280,366,289,313]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">Arizona</collectingRegion>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[407,543,289,314]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" refId="ref10037" refString="Lobl I. 2018. Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Scaphidiinae. World Catalogue of Insects. Volume 16, Brill, Leiden / Boston, XVI &amp; 418 pp." type="book" year="2018">Löbl (2018)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lobl, 1997" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="commune">
<emphasis box="[556,688,292,314]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. commune</emphasis>
Löbl, 1997
</taxonomicName>
based on probably a mislabelled specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Say, 1825" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1825" box="[151,397,353,377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexum">
<emphasis box="[151,285,355,377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. convexum</emphasis>
Say, 1825
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Casey T. L." box="[454,588,353,377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="510 - 533" refId="ref9459" refString="Casey T. L. 1893. Coleopterological Notices, V. Scaphidiidae. Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences 7: 510 - 533." type="journal article" year="1893">Casey, 1893</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Casey, 1893" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desertorum">
<emphasis box="[607,755,355,377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. desertorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Casey T. L." box="[151,285,386,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="510 - 533" refId="ref9459" refString="Casey T. L. 1893. Coleopterological Notices, V. Scaphidiidae. Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences 7: 510 - 533." type="journal article" year="1893">Casey, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1860" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1860" box="[297,586,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[297,416,388,410]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. pusillum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte J. L." box="[424,586,385,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="321 - 324" refId="ref9722" refString="LeConte J. L. 1860. Synopsis of the Scaphidiidae of the United States. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia (1860): 321 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1860">LeConte, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1860" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufulum">
<emphasis box="[644,755,388,410]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. rufulum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte J. L." box="[151,313,418,442]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="321 - 324" refId="ref9722" refString="LeConte J. L. 1860. Synopsis of the Scaphidiidae of the United States. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia (1860): 321 - 324." type="book chapter" year="1860">LeConte, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
